trials.freeResponse: Daxes beep. They are red and cylindrical in shape. Kind of short.
They rarely whistle. Purple, octagonal in shape.
They boom about half of the time. They are blue and square shaped.
They very rarely ring. The one ringing one may have been an aberration. Red and pyramidal in shape.
They always, or almost always squeak. Yellow and spindle shaped.
Tomas click about half of the time. Pink and cone shaped.

trials.response: I tested a variety of items to discover their sound producing properties. The items were various geometrically shaped objects of differing colors.
